Nigeria will come back to the organisation of volleyball competition after the Africa Volleyball Confirmation “CAVB” entrusted them to host the 2018 Men’s U21 African Nations Championship in Abuja, Nigeria,National Daily gathered.
The competition will be held on September 12 to 19, 2018 for players who were born on 1st January 1999 or after.
The final dates to confirm participation with all documents will be August 27, 2018. This championship will also act as a qualifier for the 2019 FIVB World Championship of this age category.
